# Worker Layer (`apps/worker`)

## Required queues

`ingestion`, `extraction`, `embedding`, `graph_projection`, `maintenance`

## Task rules

- Every task idempotent
- Transient errors: bounded exponential retry
- Permanent errors: dead-letter state with operator retry
- Durable business state in PostgreSQL — not only in Redis
- Record correlation ID, model, prompt version, schema version for agent tasks
- Tasks call application services — not database clients directly

## Routing

Use `task_routes` in `celery_app.py` to assign tasks to correct queues.
